
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gcalccmd` yek abzar khate farman (command line) baraye hesabat riazi va tabdil vahedeha (unit conversions) dar GNOME Calculator ast. Ba estefade az in dastoor, mitavanid hesab-ketab-haye pishrafte ra dar terminal anjam dahid. ➕➖➗

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gcalccmd --calculate='expression'` --> ➕➖➗ Mohasebeye yek expression riazi mesle `2+2*3`.
    🔹 `gcalccmd --units-from='value unit' --units-to='unit'` --> 📏 Tabdil vahedeha mesle `100 cm to inch`.
    🔹 `gcalccmd --float`  --> 🔢 Namayesh natije be soorate adad ashari (floating-point).
    🔹 `gcalccmd --help` --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gcalccmd --calculate='sqrt(16) + 5'

    🔹 Mohasebeye جذر 16 jam’e 5.

    $ gcalccmd --units-from='1 meter' --units-to='feet'

    🔹 Tabdil 1 meter be foot.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gcalccmd --calculate='sin(30 degrees)' --float

    🔹 Mohasebeye sinuse 30 daraje va namayesh natije be soorate adad ashari.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gcalccmd` command is a command-line tool for performing mathematical calculations and unit conversions using the GNOME Calculator.  It allows advanced calculations to be done directly in the terminal. ➕➖➗

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gcalccmd --calculate='expression'` --> ➕➖➗ Calculate a mathematical expression such as `2+2*3`.
    🔹 `gcalccmd --units-from='value unit' --units-to='unit'` --> 📏 Convert units, for example `100 cm to inch`.
    🔹 `gcalccmd --float`  --> 🔢 Display the result as a floating-point number.
    🔹 `gcalccmd --help` --> ❓ Display the command help.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gcalccmd --calculate='sqrt(16) + 5'

    🔹 Calculate the square root of 16 plus 5.

    $ gcalccmd --units-from='1 meter' --units-to='feet'

    🔹 Convert 1 meter to feet.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gcalccmd --calculate='sin(30 degrees)' --float

    🔹 Calculate the sine of 30 degrees and display the result as a floating-point number.
